one||Compact\n|-\n|''i Weekend''\n|Saturdays\n|\n|2017\n|''N/A''\n|Compact\n|-\n|''[[The Independent]]''\n|N/A\n|\n|1986\n|Chris Broughton\n|[[Sultan Muhammad Abuljadayel]]\n\n[[Alexander Lebedev]]\n\n[[Evgeny Lebedev]]\n|[[Liberalism in the United Kingdom|Liberal]], non-partisan\n|None{{Efn|Supported [[Sir Keir Starmer]] ([[Labour Party UK|Labour Party]]) to be [[Brexit Secretary]] and the UK's Brexit negotiator, as well as supporting [[Unionism in the United Kingdom|unionist]] candidates in Scotland, Northern Ireland and Wales.<ref>{{cite news|title=It's your vote \u2013 so think about the values you support, not just the party|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/voices/editorials/your-vote-your-values-where-the-independent-stands-in-this-most-complex-of-elections-a7773816.html|website=Independent|accessdate=7 June 2017|date=6 June 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Keir Starmer is the right person to negotiate Brexit \u2013 or at least to hold the Government to account|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/voices/editorials/keir-starmer-is-the-right-person-to-negotiate-brexit-or-at-least-to-hold-the-government-to-account-a7771381.html|website=The Independent|accessdate=7 June 2017}}</ref>}}\n|Broadsheet (1986 \u2013 2004)\nCompact (2003 \u2013 2016)\n\nOnline only (since 2016)\n|}\n\n{{notelist}}\n\n==Tabloid newspapers==\n\n:{| class=\"sortable wikitable\"\n! Title\n!Days of publication\n!Format\n! Established\n!Editor\n! Owner\n! Political<br>orientation\n! [[Endorsements in the 2019 United Kingdom general election|Political party support<br>in the 2019 general election]]\n|-\n|''[[Daily Mail]]''\n|Daily\n|Broadsheet (1896 \u2013 1971)\nTabloid (since 1971)\n|1896\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Geordie Greig]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Daily Mail and General Trust plc]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Right-wing]], [[Conservatism in the United Kingdom|conservative]]\n|rowspan=\"6\"|[[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative Party]]\n|-\n|''[[The Mail on Sunday]]''\n|Sundays\n|Tabloid\n|1982\n|-\n|''[[